I can't write.

820
01:02:52,885 --> 01:02:56,365
I can't write without you, Jo.

821
01:02:56,365 --> 01:02:59,085
I'll help you now.

822
01:02:59,085 --> 01:03:01,765
I promise.

823
01:03:06,765 --> 01:03:09,325
There's only death out there.

824
01:03:37,805 --> 01:03:39,845
I still love my wife.

825
01:03:40,245 --> 01:03:41,845
Then you should do what she says.

826
01:03:42,885 --> 01:03:44,445
Didn't she tell you to help me?

827
01:03:48,925 --> 01:03:50,205
That's not what she meant.

828
01:03:51,645 --> 01:03:56,125
[Whispers]
You have no idea what Jo meant.

829
01:03:56,125 --> 01:03:59,005
No idea.

830
01:04:10,205 --> 01:04:11,565
mm.

831
01:04:16,065 --> 01:04:16,565
aah!

832
01:04:16,765 --> 01:04:19,045
All will be revealed.

833
01:04:19,085 --> 01:04:23,585
[Gasps]

834
01:04:23,625 --> 01:04:24,305
[Sighs]

835
01:04:25,625 --> 01:04:27,425
State your name for the record.

836
01:04:30,025 --> 01:04:30,985
Michael Noonan.

837
01:04:31,665 --> 01:04:34,905
<i>As you know, I'm Kyra Devore's
guardian Ad Litem.</i>

838
01:04:35,385 --> 01:04:37,225
You know what that means,
Mr. Noonan?

839
01:04:37,905 --> 01:04:41,145
You've been appointed by
the judge to decide what's best

840
01:04:41,225 --> 01:04:43,025
for Kyra, should a custody trial
become necessary.

841
01:04:43,065 --> 01:04:45,905
Very good.

842
01:04:45,905 --> 01:04:47,865
And the judge would not,
in such a case,

843
01:04:47,905 --> 01:04:50,905
be required to base his decision
on my conclusions.

844
01:04:51,865 --> 01:04:53,905
But that's usually what happens.

845
01:04:54,745 --> 01:04:58,065
[Electric whirring]

846
01:05:05,705 --> 01:05:07,665
Sorry to be late, Elmer.

847
01:05:08,145 --> 01:05:10,825
George had trouble getting here.

848
01:05:11,985 --> 01:05:13,505
Let's turn to your first meeting

849
01:05:13,505 --> 01:05:16,145
with Mattie and Kyra Devore
on the highway, shall we?

850
01:05:16,385 --> 01:05:17,025
Sure.

851
01:05:17,905 --> 01:05:19,825
Kyra Devore was all alone.

852
01:05:20,265 --> 01:05:21,665
Her mother wasn't with her, right?

853
01:05:21,705 --> 01:05:23,225
- That's a poorly-phrased
question,

854
01:05:23,265 --> 01:05:24,665
but I suppose the answer is yes.

855
01:05:25,945 --> 01:05:27,825
I'm flattered to have
my grammar corrected

856
01:05:27,825 --> 01:05:29,145
by a best-selling author.

857
01:05:30,185 --> 01:05:31,705
Is this
a better-phrased question?

858
01:05:32,345 --> 01:05:33,945
You could have run Kyra Devore over

859
01:05:33,945 --> 01:05:36,345
'cause she was playing in
the middle of the road, correct?

860
01:05:36,465 --> 01:05:38,145
The phrasing isn't better, no.

861
01:05:38,345 --> 01:05:39,865
And my answer is absolutely not.

862
01:05:40,305 --> 01:05:41,425
I was driving the speed limit.

863
01:05:41,425 --> 01:05:43,145
