910
01:07:50,065 --> 01:07:52,305
Well, that's just...

911
01:07:52,305 --> 01:07:53,265
Writer's block?

912
01:07:55,785 --> 01:07:58,625
Mm.

913
01:07:58,665 --> 01:08:00,225
Yeah.

914
01:08:00,265 --> 01:08:02,305
My next book,

915
01:08:02,345 --> 01:08:03,825
the one that's coming out
this winter...

916
01:08:03,825 --> 01:08:05,705
<i>Yeah, I know about it.
Red shirt man, right?</i>

917
01:08:05,745 --> 01:08:06,985
Yeah.

918
01:08:07,025 --> 01:08:08,945
I wrote that book over a decade ago.

919
01:08:09,465 --> 01:08:10,545
It's a trunk novel,

920
01:08:11,185 --> 01:08:13,025
a book I never thought
should see the light of day.

921
01:08:13,065 --> 01:08:14,985
I passed it off to my agent
as a new novel

922
01:08:15,025 --> 01:08:18,385
just to keep my little...
[Sighs]

923
01:08:18,385 --> 01:08:19,825
Dilemma a secret.

924
01:08:19,905 --> 01:08:21,665
Nobody knows it's an old book?

925
01:08:21,665 --> 01:08:23,945
Nobody but you.

926
01:08:23,985 --> 01:08:27,025
Well, your secret's safe with me, sir.

927
01:08:27,105 --> 01:08:30,305
[Chuckles]

928
01:08:30,305 --> 01:08:34,305
My agent, my little agent Marty,

929
01:08:34,305 --> 01:08:35,825
after he read
the first couple of pages,

930
01:08:35,905 --> 01:08:39,945
he called me up and, uh...
[Laughs]

931
01:08:40,065 --> 01:08:42,865
You know what he...?
[Laughs]

932
01:08:42,905 --> 01:08:44,305
- You know what he said?
- What?

933
01:08:44,345 --> 01:08:46,505
This is the best thing
I've written in years.

934
01:08:46,545 --> 01:08:49,225
Well, call it classic Michael Noonan.

935
01:08:49,265 --> 01:08:50,785
Yeah, you could do.

936
