950
01:09:31,345 --> 01:09:35,145
You miss her a lot, don't you?

951
01:09:35,185 --> 01:09:37,345
Yeah.

952
01:09:37,385 --> 01:09:40,065
I saw her once.
She was very beautiful.

953
01:09:40,105 --> 01:09:42,425
Where did you see her?

954
01:09:42,465 --> 01:09:44,265
At Warrington's.

955
01:09:44,305 --> 01:09:46,065
I was, uh, a waitress there.

956
01:09:46,105 --> 01:09:48,305
And I was working a shift
with my friend Laurie Wilton,

957
01:09:48,305 --> 01:09:52,385
and... and I saw her, and I said,
"there's Mrs. Noonan,

958
01:09:52,425 --> 01:09:55,865
the writer's wife.
Isn't she pretty?"

959
01:09:55,905 --> 01:09:57,145
I think Laurie was more interested

960
01:09:57,185 --> 01:09:58,905
in the guy your wife was sitting with.

961
01:09:58,945 --> 01:10:01,665
What guy?

962
01:10:01,705 --> 01:10:02,865
He was just a guy, I guess.

963
01:10:02,905 --> 01:10:06,585
- Oh.
- Did I say something wrong?

964
01:10:06,625 --> 01:10:08,625
Yeah, I mean, who was the guy
having dinner with my wife?

965
01:10:08,625 --> 01:10:10,185
I'm... I'm sorry.
I, um...

966
01:10:10,225 --> 01:10:11,825
No, it's okay.
It's okay, it's okay.

967
01:10:11,865 --> 01:10:16,585
It's just...
I'm sorry.

968
01:10:16,625 --> 01:10:18,145
It's just...
[Clears throat]

969
01:10:18,185 --> 01:10:19,905
After Jo died,

970
01:10:19,945 --> 01:10:23,665
I found out she was pregnant.

971
