02:01:02,060 --> 02:01:04,380
Said she wanted to write an
article or a book or something.

1620
02:01:05,020 --> 02:01:09,420
Did she want to know
about Dark Score fair in 1939...

1621
02:01:10,420 --> 02:01:12,980
And Sara Tidwell?

1622
02:01:15,140 --> 02:01:16,660
Among other things, yeah.

1623
02:01:18,380 --> 02:01:19,580
But I told her...

1624
02:01:20,100 --> 02:01:22,180
I don't know anything.

1625
02:01:22,900 --> 02:01:24,860
But you were lying to her,
weren't you?

1626
02:01:25,540 --> 02:01:26,020
Hmm?

1627
02:01:26,940 --> 02:01:28,220
You do know something.

1628
02:01:28,820 --> 02:01:30,740
I bet there's lots of things you know

1629
02:01:30,740 --> 02:01:35,300
you wish you could just forget, hmm?

1630
02:01:37,460 --> 02:01:40,940
Max Devore is dead now, Edgar.

1631
02:01:41,100 --> 02:01:42,620
He can't hurt you anymore.

1632
02:01:42,620 --> 02:01:47,500
That's not always true.

1633
02:01:47,540 --> 02:01:50,780
Tell me the secret of Max Devore

1634
02:01:50,780 --> 02:01:55,620
that you keep in your heart
after all these years.

1635
02:01:57,660 --> 02:02:00,460
Tell me, Edgar.

1636
02:02:00,620 --> 02:02:02,540
Tell me what happened...

1637
02:02:02,700 --> 02:02:11,420
To you, Max Devore... And Sara Tidwell.

1638
02:02:11,460 --> 02:02:13,620
It's not about what happened

1639
02:02:13,660 --> 02:02:16,780
between me and Devore
and Sara Tidwell.

1640
02:02:16,780 --> 02:02:18,780
[Softly] What is it, then?

1641
02:02:18,780 --> 02:02:22,300
It's about what we did.

1642
02:02:22,420 --> 02:02:25,460
Tell me.

1643
02:02:25,540 --> 02:02:27,820
Just tell me.

1644
02:02:27,860 --> 02:02:31,260
It was the summer of '39...

1645
02:02:31,260 --> 02:02:33,340
[Brassy jazz music]

1646
02:02:33,340 --> 02:02:35,180
At the Dark Score fair.

1647
02:02:36,260 --> 02:02:38,100
¶ she was poor...

1648
02:02:38,100 --> 02:02:42,540
Sara Tidwell was performing
on the main stage.

1649
02:02:42,580 --> 02:02:44,940
And she was like nothing

1650
02:02:44,980 --> 02:02:48,300
we had ever seen before
around these parts.

1651
02:02:50,620 --> 02:02:54,060
it was me, Fred Dean,

1652
02:02:54,100 --> 02:02:59,220
Normal Jellison,
your grandfather Harold Noonan,

1653
02:02:59,220 --> 02:03:02,100
and mad Max Devore.

1654
02:03:02,180 --> 02:03:06,500
Even then, Max was
the man with the plan.

1655
02:03:06,540 --> 02:03:09,500
And everyone knew
that he would eventually

1656
02:03:09,540 --> 02:03:12,940
run Dark Score Lake

1657
02:03:12,980 --> 02:03:16,500
and become a very rich
and important man in the world.

1658
02:03:16,540 --> 02:03:19,940
It was Max's idea to go to the show.

1659
02:03:19,980 --> 02:03:21,220
