1696
02:05:09,340 --> 02:05:10,580
Please don't hurt my little girl.

1697
02:05:10,660 --> 02:05:12,660
I'll do anything...

1698
02:05:12,820 --> 02:05:13,900
Anything you say!
Please!

1699
02:05:14,060 --> 02:05:16,340
You already are doing anything I say.

1700
02:05:17,580 --> 02:05:18,340
Get her.
[Sobbing]

1701
02:05:18,740 --> 02:05:20,220
You think we can leave any witnesses?

1702
02:05:20,260 --> 02:05:21,860
Even I can't get us out of this one.

1703
02:05:21,860 --> 02:05:23,620
Now catch that little girl
and take her out to the lake.

1704
02:05:23,660 --> 02:05:26,060
No! Oh, God, !

1705
02:05:26,740 --> 02:05:28,460
Please, please...

1706
02:05:28,500 --> 02:05:30,460
Please, I'll do anything.

1707
02:05:30,500 --> 02:05:34,020
Please just don't hurt my little girl.

1708
02:05:34,100 --> 02:05:36,580
Please.
Please!

1709
02:05:39,580 --> 02:05:41,100
Help, I'm drown...

1710
02:05:41,140 --> 02:05:43,340
Please, don't hurt my baby!

1711
02:05:46,540 --> 02:05:47,620
Please, God!

1712
02:05:47,620 --> 02:05:50,020
No, no, no!

1713
02:05:50,220 --> 02:05:51,900
Shut that bitch up.
Somebody's going to hear her.

1714
02:05:52,100 --> 02:05:54,260
Oh, no!
No, stop!

1715
02:05:59,820 --> 02:06:01,660
[Coughing]

1716
02:06:03,980 --> 02:06:06,860
[Screaming]

1717
02:06:12,300 --> 02:06:15,060
[Spits]

1718
02:06:15,460 --> 02:06:16,300
You...

1719
02:06:17,100 --> 02:06:20,500
And your kin are cursed!

1720
02:06:22,220 --> 02:06:24,740
You and your sons

1721
02:06:25,380 --> 02:06:29,060
are going to do to your daughters
what you've done to mine.

1722
02:06:30,100 --> 02:06:32,060
With your own hands,

1723
02:06:32,220 --> 02:06:35,060
you will murder your daughters.

1724
02:06:35,940 --> 02:06:37,580
And with their own hands,

1725
02:06:37,660 --> 02:06:41,100
your sons are going
to murder their daughters.

1726
02:06:42,420 --> 02:06:46,220
A curse on you and yours

1727
02:06:46,300 --> 02:06:49,180
until you're all gone!

1728
02:06:49,580 --> 02:06:53,180
[Sobbing]

1729
02:07:04,380 --> 02:07:06,700
Max told us
that we could never mention

1730
02:07:06,700 --> 02:07:08,900
a word of it to anyone

1731
02:07:08,940 --> 02:07:11,460
for as long as we lived,

1732
02:07:11,500 --> 02:07:13,700
that it would ruin us all.

1733
02:07:13,740 --> 02:07:19,060
He had us bury their bodies
out in the woods.

1734
02:07:19,100 --> 02:07:21,100
And that was the end of Sara Tidwell

1735
02:07:22,900 --> 02:07:24,100
and her daughter, Kisha.

1736
02:08:29,620 --> 02:08:30,700
[Knock on door]

1737
02:08:33,900 --> 02:08:35,340
- Hi.
- Hey.

1738
02:08:35,820 --> 02:08:37,540
- Come in.
- I made it.

1739
02:08:37,700 --> 02:08:38,980
[Clears throat]

1740
02:08:43,180 --> 02:08:44,780
- Y-you don't...

1741
02:08:46,660 --> 02:08:48,060
[Both chuckle awkwardly]

1742
02:08:50,260 --> 02:08:51,820
[Clears throat]

1743
02:08:53,820 --> 02:08:54,980
"Kiss the cook".

1744
02:08:58,340 --> 02:08:59,140
Well?

1745
02:09:01,220 --> 02:09:01,940
Well.

1746
02:09:27,300 --> 02:09:28,380
[Giggles]

1747
02:09:30,380 --> 02:09:31,500
I think we have a visitor.

1748
02:09:33,500 --> 02:09:35,980
- Hi, Mr. Mike.
- Hi, Miss Ky.

1749
02:09:37,420 --> 02:09:38,180
How's it going?

1750
02:09:38,780 --> 02:09:40,300
- Good.
- Good.

1751
02:09:40,460 --> 02:09:41,180
What you up to?

1752
02:09:41,580 --> 02:09:44,060
Will you read me
my bedtime story, please?

1753
02:09:44,180 --> 02:09:46,540
Sweetheart, I told you,
no begging Mr. Mike.

1754
02:09:46,660 --> 02:09:49,100
I would be more than happy
to read you a bedtime story.

1755
02:09:49,100 --> 02:09:50,580
Come on.
Hooray!

1756
02:09:53,540 --> 02:09:54,660
How can I refuse?

1757
02:09:54,820 --> 02:09:56,020
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

1758
02:10:02,220 --> 02:10:06,180
"For her birthday, Kim's mom
invited her to the fair

1759
02:10:06,380 --> 02:10:08,100
"that just came to town for the week.

1760
02:10:08,620 --> 02:10:10,620
"'Get dressed, my love,
and we'll go.'

1761
02:10:10,940 --> 02:10:11,780
"'okay, mom.'

1762
02:10:12,700 --> 02:10:15,980
"at the fair, many people
were waiting to buy tickets.

1763
02:10:16,540 --> 02:10:19,900
"From far away, she saw the big wheel.

1764
02:10:20,460 --> 02:10:22,300
Kim was so happy."

1765
02:10:23,500 --> 02:10:25,420
I dreamed about you the other night.

1766
02:10:27,500 --> 02:10:28,100
You did?

1767
02:10:30,500 --> 02:10:31,340
- [Yawns]
Mm-hmm.

1768
02:10:33,780 --> 02:10:34,940
And what was your dream about?

1769
02:10:36,060 --> 02:10:37,340
A circus...

1770
02:10:41,060 --> 02:10:41,580
Or...

1771
02:10:42,380 --> 02:10:44,260
A fair or something.

1772
02:10:44,900 --> 02:10:45,700
And...

1773
02:10:47,740 --> 02:10:50,180
What happened in this dream
of yours the other night?

1774
02:10:51,180 --> 02:10:53,300
You were trying to save me
from the bad men,

1775
02:10:54,060 --> 02:10:55,780
and the mad lady was singing.

1776
02:10:56,660 --> 02:10:59,340
And we hid in a real scary place.

1777
02:10:59,860 --> 02:11:02,620
But the mad lady's little girl
was hiding, too.

1778
02:11:03,380 --> 02:11:05,100
[Thunder rumbles]

1779
02:11:05,140 --> 02:11:06,420
And that girl...

1780
02:11:07,780 --> 02:11:09,620
Was she the mad lady's daughter?

1781
02:11:10,300 --> 02:11:11,180
- Mm-hmm.

1782
02:11:14,460 --> 02:11:15,420
How do you know that?

1783
02:11:16,100 --> 02:11:18,060
Because she told me, silly.

1784
02:11:19,820 --> 02:11:20,700
[Chuckles with relief] She did?

1785
02:11:21,500 --> 02:11:23,060
- Mm-hmm.
She's my friend.

1786
02:11:23,620 --> 02:11:25,740
Oh, she's your friend.

1787
02:11:28,740 --> 02:11:29,580
Since when?

1788
02:11:30,660 --> 02:11:31,500
Ever since...

1789
02:11:32,220 --> 02:11:36,180
Her mommy, the mad lady,
made my daddy try to...

1790
02:11:38,100 --> 02:11:39,020
Hurt me.

1791
02:11:43,860 --> 02:11:45,980
It was the mad lady
who made your daddy do that?

1792
02:11:46,740 --> 02:11:47,460
- Mm-hmm.

1793
02:11:47,860 --> 02:11:49,540
Her daughter's name is Kisha.

1794
02:11:50,220 --> 02:11:51,860
And it's called a curse.

1795
02:11:54,180 --> 02:11:55,020
A curse.

1796
02:11:57,060 --> 02:11:59,420
Can we finish reading
my book now, Mr. Mike?

1797
02:12:02,740 --> 02:12:04,940
Sure.
On one condition.

1798
02:12:06,460 --> 02:12:07,540
You call me "Mike."

1799
02:12:08,180 --> 02:12:09,060
Okay, Mike.

1800
02:12:09,500 --> 02:12:12,460
It's a deal.
It's a deal.

1801
02:12:35,200 --> 02:12:35,840
How is she?

1802
02:12:36,200 --> 02:12:37,440
She's good.
She's, uh...

1803
02:12:37,960 --> 02:12:39,120
Out like a light.

1804
02:12:41,800 --> 02:12:43,200
[Sighs] What's the matter?

1805
02:12:44,040 --> 02:12:46,560
She, uh... I don't know...
She mentioned something

1806
02:12:46,600 --> 02:12:49,200
- about a little girl named Kisha.
- Oh, yeah.

1807
02:12:49,240 --> 02:12:50,680
That's her imaginary friend, Kisha,

1808
02:12:50,760 --> 02:12:51,880
but it's okay, 'cause the doctor said

1809
02:12:51,880 --> 02:12:54,440
that she's perfectly normal
and I don't have a crazy kid,

1810
02:12:54,440 --> 02:12:56,200
so that's...
That's good.

1811
02:12:58,880 --> 02:12:59,800
So the funeral?

1812
02:13:01,080 --> 02:13:02,240
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have made you go.

1813
02:13:02,240 --> 02:13:03,440
No, no, no, no, no,
actually that's been the

1814
02:13:03,440 --> 02:13:04,600
best part of the last
couple of days for me...

1815
02:13:05,480 --> 02:13:08,280
Seeing that old bastard lowered
into the ground once and for all.

1816
02:13:09,400 --> 02:13:10,680
- Yeah.
- I, um...

1817
02:13:13,360 --> 02:13:15,480
I learned about the disappearance

1818
02:13:15,480 --> 02:13:17,920
of Sara Tidwell today

1819
02:13:17,960 --> 02:13:21,040
from an old man in a rest home,

1820
02:13:21,080 --> 02:13:25,520
who, it turns out, Jo had also
visited before she died.

1821
02:13:27,600 --> 02:13:30,640
Do you know who Sara Tidwell is?

1822
02:13:30,680 --> 02:13:34,280
Lance, my husband, used
to listen to her music before...

1823
02:13:37,960 --> 02:13:40,080
I, uh... I didn't know
she disappeared.

1824
02:13:40,160 --> 02:13:42,520
In 1939.

1825
02:13:42,560 --> 02:13:44,640
Only she didn't really
disappear... she was killed.

1826
02:13:44,640 --> 02:13:47,160
After she played
at the Dark Score fair one day,

1827
02:13:47,160 --> 02:13:49,480
she was raped.

1828
02:13:51,600 --> 02:13:54,360
And then she and
her little daughter, Kisha,

1829
02:13:54,360 --> 02:13:56,000
were killed by a group of teenagers,

1830
02:13:56,000 --> 02:13:58,320
led by the young Max Devore.

1831
02:13:59,640 --> 02:14:00,680
Oh, my God.

1832
02:14:00,800 --> 02:14:02,800
Which would explain why...

1833
02:14:03,800 --> 02:14:05,600
Lance got interested in her music

1834
02:14:05,760 --> 02:14:07,320
before he tried to kill Kyra.

1835
02:14:09,640 --> 02:14:10,480
Tell me.

1836
02:14:13,360 --> 02:14:14,200
A curse...

1837
02:14:15,400 --> 02:14:18,640
On all the young men who killed
Sara Tidwell and her little girl.

1838
02:14:20,800 --> 02:14:22,040
With her dying breath,

1839
02:14:23,240 --> 02:14:24,360
